Pre-existing directories and files created for the agent:

 1. Directory: /home/user/baseline_configs/
 2. Directory: /home/user/secure_templates/

 3. /home/user/baseline_configs/nginx.conf  (contents, ending with “\n”)

worker_processes  1;
events {
    worker_connections  1024;
}

http {
    server_tokens on;
    include       mime.types;
    default_type  application/octet-stream;
    sendfile        on;
    keepalive_timeout  65;
}

 4. /home/user/secure_templates/nginx.conf  (contents, ending with “\n”)

worker_processes  auto;
events {
    worker_connections  2048;
}

http {
    server_tokens off;
    include       mime.types;
    default_type  application/octet-stream;
    sendfile        on;
    keepalive_timeout  30;
    add_header X-Content-Type-Options nosniff;
}

 Expected artefacts after successful completion:

  • Directory /home/user/compliance_patches/ must exist.

  • /home/user/compliance_patches/nginx_security.patch  
    Exact unified diff content (timestamps may differ):

--- /home/user/baseline_configs/nginx.conf
+++ /home/user/secure_templates/nginx.conf
@@ -1,12 +1,13 @@
-worker_processes  1;
+worker_processes  auto;
 events {
-    worker_connections  1024;
+    worker_connections  2048;
 }

 http {
-    server_tokens on;
+    server_tokens off;
     include       mime.types;
     default_type  application/octet-stream;
     sendfile        on;
-    keepalive_timeout  65;
+    keepalive_timeout  30;
+    add_header X-Content-Type-Options nosniff;
 }
+

  • Patched file /home/user/baseline_configs/nginx.conf  
    must be byte-identical to the secure template shown above.

  • Backup file /home/user/baseline_configs/nginx.conf.orig  
    must retain the original insecure contents (“worker_processes  1;”
    etc.).

  • /home/user/compliance_patches/patch_apply.log  
    must contain exactly three newline-terminated lines:

PATCH STATUS: SUCCESS
ORIGINAL_BACKUP: /home/user/baseline_configs/nginx.conf.orig
UPDATED_FILE_CHECKSUM: <computed_sha256_of_patched_file>

    The test harness will independently calculate SHA-256 on the patched
    nginx.conf and compare it with the value in line 3.

 Permissions: all files should be readable/writable by uid 1000 (user),
 group and others default umask 022.
